    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The reason why we need this optimization is because existence checks on a large (e.g. 30GB) LevelDB are very expensive, so maybe we could use a separate LevelDB where we'd keep just the hash of nodes known to be present in the chain DB. This separate LevelDB would be created when the StateDownloader starts, passed on to HexaryTrieSync, and destroyed when StateDownloader exits",
